{"id":"week","term":"Week","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>From the beginning, time was divided into weeks, each consisting of six days of working and one of rest (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:2\">Gen. 2:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:3\">3</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 7:10\">7:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 8:10\">8:10</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 8:12\">12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 29:28\">29:28</a>). The references to this division of days becomes afterwards more frequent (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 34:22\">Ex. 34:22</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 12:5\">Lev. 12:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 28:26\">Num. 28:26</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 16:16\">Deut. 16:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 8:13\">2 Chr. 8:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 5:24\">Jer. 5:24</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Daniel 9:24\">Dan. 9:24-27</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Daniel 10:2\">10:2</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Daniel 10:3\">3</a>). It has been found to exist among almost all nations.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 2:2","Genesis 1:3","Genesis 7:10","Genesis 8:10","Genesis 8:12","Genesis 29:28","Exodus 34:22","Leviticus 12:5","Numbers 28:26","Deuteronomy 16:16","2 Chronicles 8:13","Jeremiah 5:24","Daniel 9:24","Daniel 10:2","Daniel 10:3"]}